May is ‘Family Month’ in Korea 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦
Children's Day, Mother's Day, Adoption Day, and Husband and Wife Day are all celebrated in May, making it a special month to think about the meaning of family.
Since ancient times, Korea has been very family-oriented, emphasizing the importance of familial relationships. In the past, most households had a family motto plaque called a 'Gahwamansaseong' hung in the house that carried the meaning of 'everything will go well if the family is happy'.

Family is precious, but we often forget how important it is. In celebration of Family Month, we hope you take the time to express your gratitude to your family and close friends💛

And a big thank you to our other family members, the BOJ BEAUTIES, as well!

Do you remember Binghegak Lee, who we introduced to you on Women's Day? ☺️

The book 'Regulation Book (Gyuhap Chongseo)' written by Bing Heo-gak Lee is a great inspiration for the launch of Beauty of Joseon.
This book contains ways to enrich women's lives to be more convenient in daily life such as skincare tips, clothing, farming, prenatal care, parenting advice, and organizing homes.

Inspired by this book, our brand made products from herbal ingredients that have been used since the Joseon Dynasty.
Oriental medicine ingredients are healthy ingredients that have been consumed as medicinal herbs and food for a long time, and they are also excellent skincare ingredients.
Whenever we make a new skincare product, we think about suitable herbal ingredients for each skin type and combine modern ingredients that create the most synergy to make a great product with the intent of “giving a present”. 🤍

For full information check out our blog (link in BIO) 🌿

Happy Thursday! It has been almost 2 months since we launched Relief Sun (time flies!) 🍃
First things first, thank you so much guys for the amazing support and love that you show us. We truly made every effort to make it work on every skin type and tone! 
Let us share some key points that have been mentioned in the reviews! 💚

[Lightweight texture] It has a very lightweight cream formula and it moisturizes your skin immediately without leaving a sticky or heavy feeling. 

[Makeup friendly] Because of its light texture, it sits stably under your makeup without peeling or a cakey finish. 

[No white cast] It does not leave a white cast. For darker skin tones, it may seem that it has a blue finish, BUT it disappears perfectly after you spread it on your skin.

What is "Gwalsa"? And how to use it? 🤔
I guess most of you guys are wodering what it is and how it helps to?

🍃Ceramic gwalsa (which is commonly called as 'Guasha' in the market), used in traditional folk remedies since ancient times, repeatedly stimulates each part of the body to release meridians and activate acupuncture points. Ancient pottery is the material optimized for traditional gwalsa therapy. ​
So it's been a long time since ceramic massager-gwalsa, had become popular in Korea, cause of it multiply finctioning.

🍃Our new 'Gwalsa' has a very unique shape, and it's easy to use for both skin and body. The weight is also not too heavy or light so that it can be used on any part of your body with appropriate pressure.

🍃Gwalsa massage stimulates the meridians, paths that connect the important reaction points between the skin and muscles, bringing a bright tone to skin, and also has the effect of controlling facial edema, facial asymmetry, and facial muscles. ​

Hi beauties! Just following up on Radiance Cleansing Balm latest updates🤍
After the renewed version was launched, we heard the feedback about sore eyes when using it. So we did a second renewal right away, and the upgraded version was released in mid-September.
So here's the recap:
🔘Original version: contained fragrances, the texture wasn't very stable in humid conditions
🔘1st upgrade (July, 2021): larger size (80ml → 100ml), excluded fragrances, more stable and solid texture, improved packaging
🔘2nd upgrade (September, 2021): improved discomfort regarding sore eyes from the 1st upgrade version
Is there anyone who’s tried the 2nd upgrade version? We'd love to hear your thoughts! 🤍

Hi there! Today we'd like to talk about serum for sensitive skin types and provide some recommendations.
As you already know it's very important to find your own products and ways to take care of your skin. So here is a little solution to help you out with your skincare routine ✨
BOJ has 4 different types of serum and each of them has their own benefits. One of them is Glow deep serum, in which the main ingredient is rice! 🍚 
The strongest benefit of this serum is that it helps to fight pigmentation and also brings a healthy brightness to your skin.
It doesn't contain any fragrances or essential oils and has a watery texture without a sticky finish. It also works well along with other serums and ingredients. 
(*Make sure to check your skin condition before mixing with other ingredients!)

Skincare basics for beginners 🫧
Layering the skincare starts with learning the texture ✨
Always start light & build up: cleanser → toner → (mask) → essence → serum → moisturizer → SPF 💧☁️✨
 
Pro tip: Think humectants, emollients, occlusives. Hydrate, soften, then seal to get glowy skin.
